  "body": "**Is your feature request related to a problem? Please describe.**\r\n\r\nThis is from https://github.com/ChainSafe/lodestar/pull/3178#issue-996944825\r\n\r\nIf we use functions and constants of other modules in a for loop, tsc would compile it from\r\n\r\n```ts\r\nfor (let i = 0; i < statuses.length; i++) {\r\n    const status = statuses[i];\r\n    if (hasMarkers(status.flags, FLAG_ELIGIBLE_ATTESTER)) {\r\n```\r\nto\r\n```js\r\nfor (let i = 0; i < statuses.length; i++) {\r\n        const status = statuses[i];\r\n        if ((0, util_1.hasMarkers)(status.flags, util_1.FLAG_ELIGIBLE_ATTESTER)) {\r\n            let inactivityScore = inactivityScores[i];\r\n```\r\nas we can see, it keeps accesing `util_1.*` in a for loop and it makes the code slow, we should instead import functions/constants outside of the for loop\r\n```ts\r\n// this avoids importing FLAG_ELIGIBLE_ATTESTER inside the for loop, check the compiled code\r\n    const { FLAG_ELIGIBLE_ATTESTER, FLAG_PREV_TARGET_ATTESTER_OR_UNSLASHED, hasMarkers } = constants;\r\n    for (let i = 0; i < statuses.length; i++) {\r\n        const status = statuses[i];\r\n        if (hasMarkers(status.flags, FLAG_ELIGIBLE_ATTESTER)) {\r\n```\r\n\r\nin the case of `processInactivityUpdates`, this gives a 10% improvement\r\n\r\n**Describe the solution you'd like**\r\n\r\nWe should apply the same fix to other places in `beacon-state-transition` and check the performance gain there\r\n",
